    "extras": [
      "Auschwitz-Birkenau works best as a full day trip from Krakow: memorial entry is free, official educator-led tours are about ₹3,150, and train or bus transport to Oświęcim is usually another ₹315–₹525 each way.",
      "Reserve Auschwitz, Schindler’s Factory, and Warsaw Uprising Museum slots in advance in peak season; all three can sell out several days ahead.",
      "Jakdojade is the most reliable app for trams, buses, and metro in Warsaw, Krakow, Wroclaw, and Gdansk; Bolt is usually cheaper than airport taxis for late arrivals.",
      "Most larger stores stay closed on many Sundays, so use Żabka convenience shops or station retail if you need groceries on arrival.",
      "If you want a mountain add-on, use Krakow as the jump-off for Zakopane by bus or train in about 2.5–3 hours, but keep it outside this core city route."
